reviewText: and it's screw handles are ribbed and very easy to grasp.Nicely constructed.
Well built. Thumb screws are very ergonomic. I use these cables with standard external modems like the USRobotics 56K faxmodems. Good value for the money.

reviewerName: Jeffrey A. Hensley Hensley's Bluegrass Music
reviewText: What more can you say. It works like expected. The cable didn't appear to be cheaply made and all hardware interfaced using the cable worked perfectly.

This is a decent cable for the price. The connection of the cable to the connector is rugged and will resist breaking easily. Cable is well insulated and connectors are of typical Belkin quality. Have used this in several environments including in the lab setting with satisfactory performance.
Just what I needed to allow my users to connect to our CNC machines from their laptops. Great price, I couldn't make them for this price.

This is basically just a DE-9 to DB-25 adapter. It has the normal RS-232 specified pinouts on both ends, so it should work with almost anything. It will not work with things that use a proprietary pinout, such as point of sale (POS) machines. We use these for factory hardware and label printers.
